00:06:57.726 --> 00:07:00.686 A:middle
up something that I saw on
the news just a few days ago.

00:07:01.476 --> 00:07:03.796 A:middle
This is Brandon Moss of
the Cleveland Indians,

00:07:03.796 --> 00:07:08.106 A:middle
and he hit his 100th career
home run last Tuesday.

00:07:08.746 --> 00:07:10.896 A:middle
Obviously, it's a huge milestone
if you are a baseball player.

00:07:10.896 --> 00:07:12.576 A:middle
Not a lot of people do this.

00:07:13.146 --> 00:07:15.156 A:middle
And you can imagine how much

00:07:15.156 --> 00:07:17.376 A:middle
that ball would mean
to him to have it.

00:07:18.296 --> 00:07:22.636 A:middle
It turns out the ball was hit
into the Indians' bull pen,

00:07:22.636 --> 00:07:26.366 A:middle
and his teammates decided to
play a bit of a prank on him.

00:07:27.076 --> 00:07:29.446 A:middle
They decided to hold
it for ransom.

00:07:31.056 --> 00:07:34.046 A:middle
And this is the list of
things they asked for.

00:07:34.806 --> 00:07:39.226 A:middle
[Laughter] Apple Watches,
iPads, MacBook Airs, iPhones.

00:07:40.306 --> 00:07:41.106 A:middle
It's unbelievable.

00:07:41.106 --> 00:07:42.736 A:middle
It's a shopping list
for the Apple Store.

00:07:43.516 --> 00:07:49.166 A:middle
[Applause]

00:07:49.666 --> 00:07:52.456 A:middle
Now, Brandon would have
had to raid an Apple Store

00:07:52.626 --> 00:07:53.816 A:middle
to get that ball back.

00:07:54.206 --> 00:07:58.076 A:middle
That didn't seem quite right
to us, and so what we're going

00:07:58.076 --> 00:08:00.086 A:middle
to do is we're going
to pay the ransom.

WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:181083,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

00:07:58.076 --> 00:08:00.086 A:middle
to do is we're going
to pay the ransom.

00:08:01.366 --> 00:08:06.796 A:middle
And I have the ball right here.

00:08:07.516 --> 00:08:15.026 A:middle
[Applause]

00:08:15.526 --> 00:08:19.266 A:middle
We are giving the ball to
Brandon, and we are going

00:08:19.296 --> 00:08:22.646 A:middle
to give everything his
teammates asked for to them

00:08:22.646 --> 00:08:23.856 A:middle
so everybody is happy.

00:08:24.516 --> 00:08:27.266 A:middle
So congratulations, Brandon,
on a hundred home runs,

00:08:27.586 --> 00:08:28.746 A:middle
and good luck on
the next hundred.

00:08:29.516 --> 00:08:34.256 A:middle
[Applause]

