in app launching,
a 2x improvement

00:20:25.776 --> 00:20:27.666 A:middle
in the snappiness
of switching apps.

00:20:28.546 --> 00:20:32.326 A:middle
The time to get first Mail
messages, twice as fast.

00:20:32.326 --> 00:20:35.516 A:middle
Opening a PDF in preview,
four times as fast.

00:20:35.516 --> 00:20:38.926 A:middle
But we've also made deep
architectural improvements,

00:20:39.336 --> 00:20:41.436 A:middle
and that brings us to Metal.

00:20:42.516 --> 00:20:44.916 A:middle
[Applause]

00:20:45.416 --> 00:20:45.846 A:middle
Thank you.

00:20:46.036 --> 00:20:49.276 A:middle
Last year we introduced
Metal at WWDC as a way

00:20:49.276 --> 00:20:52.546 A:middle
to accelerate graphics in
high-performance games.

00:20:52.916 --> 00:20:55.156 A:middle
It takes the overhead
out of OpenGL,

00:20:55.466 --> 00:20:57.036 A:middle
providing a high-performance API

00:20:57.346 --> 00:20:59.646 A:middle
that gives the game
direct access to the power

00:20:59.646 --> 00:21:01.086 A:middle
of the underlying
graphics hardware.

