Well, this year we are
bringing Metal to the Mac.

00:21:05.266 --> 00:21:06.726 A:middle
And we are doing more than that.

00:21:07.606 --> 00:21:10.496 A:middle
Because we are taking the
graphic stacks on which apps

00:21:10.786 --> 00:21:13.386 A:middle
on OS X are built, Core
Animation and Core Graphics,

00:21:13.686 --> 00:21:17.556 A:middle
and moving them from OpenGL to
run natively on top of Metal,

00:21:18.126 --> 00:21:20.016 A:middle
making everything you do faster.

00:21:20.016 --> 00:21:22.366 A:middle
We are seeing 50
percent improvements

00:21:22.366 --> 00:21:25.696 A:middle
in rendering performance
and a 40 percent reduction

00:21:25.696 --> 00:21:27.986 A:middle
in the amount of CPU
necessary to do graphics.

00:21:28.316 --> 00:21:30.746 A:middle
That means improved performance
for your applications

00:21:30.836 --> 00:21:32.516 A:middle
and better battery life.

00:21:32.686 --> 00:21:35.526 A:middle
But the benefits of
Metal don't stop there.

00:21:35.986 --> 00:21:39.386 A:middle
Metal's also great for
high-performance apps.

00:21:39.656 --> 00:21:43.456 A:middle
In fact, Metal combines
the compute power of OpenCL

00:21:43.686 --> 00:21:45.136 A:middle
and the graphics power of OpenGL

00:21:45.136 --> 00:21:49.376 A:middle
in a higher performance
API that does both.

00:21:50.196 --> 00:21:51.506 A:middle
And what we've seen from working

00:21:51.506 --> 00:21:54.856 A:middle
with early pro developers
is really phenomenal.

00:21:55.266 --> 00:21:57.476 A:middle
Adobe came in and,
in short order,

00:21:57.476 --> 00:22:00.436 A:middle
was able to deliver an
eight times improvement

WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:181083,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

00:21:57.476 --> 00:22:00.436 A:middle
was able to deliver an
eight times improvement

00:22:00.856 --> 00:22:03.656 A:middle
in their rendering effects
inside of After Effects,

00:22:04.216 --> 00:22:07.076 A:middle
and they have been able
to take the drawing engine

00:22:07.146 --> 00:22:10.576 A:middle
in Illustrator, move it on top
of Metal, and take kinds of UI

00:22:10.746 --> 00:22:13.946 A:middle
that previously was
noninteractive,

00:22:13.946 --> 00:22:16.256 A:middle
like zoom of extremely
detailed drawings,

00:22:16.856 --> 00:22:18.806 A:middle
and make it completely flawless

00:22:18.806 --> 00:22:20.586 A:middle
and interactive,
thanks to Metal.

00:22:21.406 --> 00:22:23.856 A:middle
Adobe is so pleased with this
they said they are committed

00:22:23.856 --> 00:22:25.466 A:middle
to adopting Metal
on their OS X apps,

00:22:26.386 --> 00:22:28.126 A:middle
seeing performance
increases up to 8x.

00:22:28.756 --> 00:22:30.716 A:middle
They are excited
about what it can do

00:22:30.716 --> 00:22:32.116 A:middle
for their Creative Cloud users.

00:22:32.886 --> 00:22:36.076 A:middle
Of course, Metal is
also fantastic for games

00:22:36.076 --> 00:22:37.936 A:middle
with a 10x improvement.

00:22:37.936 --> 00:22:41.956 A:middle
That's ten times improvement
in drawing performance.

00:22:42.806 --> 00:22:46.686 A:middle
So we brought in Epic to
see what they could do

00:22:46.686 --> 00:22:49.546 A:middle
in short order, and the
results are really phenomenal.

00:22:49.546 --> 00:22:52.376 A:middle
I'd like to welcome to
the stage Josh Adams

00:22:52.376 --> 00:22:54.126 A:middle
and Billy Bramer
for a quick demo.

00:22:55.401 --> 00:22:57.401 A:middle
[Applause]

00:22:57.786 --> 00:22:59.606 A:middle
&gt;&gt; Thank you, Craig.

WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:181083,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

00:23:00.206 --> 00:23:01.906 A:middle
Thank you very much for
having us here today.

00:23:03.026 --> 00:23:06.286 A:middle
So last year Metal
revolutionized graphics on iOS,

00:23:06.786 --> 00:23:10.826 A:middle
and now Apple's amazed us again
by bringing Metal to the Mac.

00:23:11.386 --> 00:23:13.686 A:middle
Of course, this is
great news for games,

00:23:14.126 --> 00:23:17.006 A:middle
but also for the tools that
we use to make those games.

00:23:17.776 --> 00:23:20.686 A:middle
Here you are seeing Epic's
upcoming multiplayer title

00:23:20.936 --> 00:23:23.146 A:middle
Fortnite, running
entirely on Metal.

00:23:23.146 --> 00:23:25.956 A:middle
We are modifying it directly
within the Unreal Engine,

00:23:26.316 --> 00:23:28.866 A:middle
a development tool that powers
many of today's best games.

00:23:29.736 --> 00:23:31.516 A:middle
It's quite a bit going
on in this scene, though,

00:23:31.606 --> 00:23:32.636 A:middle
so let's break it down.

00:23:33.486 --> 00:23:36.096 A:middle
First, there are
64 different layers

00:23:36.096 --> 00:23:38.296 A:middle
of rendering effects,
and that's a lot.

00:23:39.686 --> 00:23:41.116 A:middle
All combining together, though,

00:23:41.116 --> 00:23:43.536 A:middle
to produce what you
see on the scene today.

00:23:43.536 --> 00:23:47.606 A:middle
If we go into a simple wireframe
mode, you can see the thousands

00:23:47.606 --> 00:23:49.276 A:middle
of building blocks that
make up this world.

00:23:49.856 --> 00:23:53.566 A:middle
We can start to add in layers,
flat shading, detailed lighting,

00:23:54.096 --> 00:23:57.496 A:middle
runtime shadows, and finally
we combine them all together

00:23:57.496 --> 00:24:00.136 A:middle
to bring Fortnite's fun and
lighthearted aesthetic to life.

WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:181083,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

00:23:57.496 --> 00:24:00.136 A:middle
to bring Fortnite's fun and
lighthearted aesthetic to life.

00:24:00.136 --> 00:24:02.326 A:middle
The interesting thing
here, though,

00:24:02.536 --> 00:24:04.796 A:middle
is that all of the effects
you are seeing are being done

00:24:04.796 --> 00:24:06.006 A:middle
completely in real-time.

00:24:06.536 --> 00:24:08.846 A:middle
Notice how the shadows and
objects interact nicely

00:24:08.846 --> 00:24:10.226 A:middle
as Josh moves the car around.

00:24:11.036 --> 00:24:14.086 A:middle
Finally, we can change the
time of day on the fly,

00:24:14.406 --> 00:24:16.836 A:middle
dramatically altering the
mood of the entire scene.

00:24:17.716 --> 00:24:20.086 A:middle
All of this is thanks to
the efficiency of Metal.

00:24:20.606 --> 00:24:23.796 A:middle
In fact, we are seeing
a 70 percent reduction

00:24:23.796 --> 00:24:27.086 A:middle
in CPUs compared to OpenGL,
enabling developers like us

00:24:27.326 --> 00:24:28.736 A:middle
to create richer 3D worlds.

00:24:29.646 --> 00:24:33.056 A:middle
Speaking of those worlds, let's
hop into the game, Fortnite.

00:24:34.346 --> 00:24:36.136 A:middle
Now, if you've ever
built a pillow fort

00:24:36.136 --> 00:24:38.096 A:middle
and battled imaginary
monsters with your friends,

00:24:38.446 --> 00:24:39.766 A:middle
you already know how
to play Fortnite.

00:24:40.226 --> 00:24:42.196 A:middle
This is the end-of-the-world
scenario you have been training

00:24:42.256 --> 00:24:43.276 A:middle
for since you were a kid.

00:24:44.276 --> 00:24:46.676 A:middle
It's a beautifully
stylized universe.

00:24:46.756 --> 00:24:48.426 A:middle
You can destroy anything
you want.

00:24:49.056 --> 00:24:50.936 A:middle
Gather resources
and build a fort.

00:24:50.936 --> 00:24:53.036 A:middle
So let's go ahead
and wreck this car.

00:24:55.336 --> 00:24:56.346 A:middle
Gather its metal.

00:24:57.246 --> 00:24:59.736 A:middle
And continue our wanton
destruction by chopping

00:24:59.736 --> 00:25:01.556 A:middle
down this tree to get
some wood for later.

WEBVTT
