00:29:57.106 --> 00:30:01.626 A:middle
from Utah last August" can
instantly show you the right

00:30:01.686 --> 00:30:03.476 A:middle
photos from your photo library.

00:30:04.046 --> 00:30:07.066 A:middle
And Siri's really great
at taking reminders.

00:30:07.526 --> 00:30:09.896 A:middle
Now you can ask Siri
things like "remind me

00:30:09.896 --> 00:30:13.076 A:middle
to grab my coffee off the
roof of my car when I get in."

00:30:13.356 --> 00:30:15.596 A:middle
Because Siri knows now when
you've gotten in the car.

00:30:16.466 --> 00:30:18.796 A:middle
And of course, we often want
to take reminders about things

00:30:18.796 --> 00:30:21.226 A:middle
that we are looking at on our
device, some content inside

00:30:21.226 --> 00:30:22.536 A:middle
of our app, maybe a Safari.

00:30:23.246 --> 00:30:26.366 A:middle
Now you can say things
like "remind me about this

00:30:26.526 --> 00:30:29.836 A:middle
when I get home," and that
reminder refers right back

00:30:30.226 --> 00:30:32.296 A:middle
with a link to specifically
what you were looking

00:30:32.366 --> 00:30:33.906 A:middle
at when you took that reminder.

00:30:34.986 --> 00:30:36.716 A:middle
So Siri is a great assistant.

00:30:37.466 --> 00:30:40.226 A:middle
But the best assistants
are proactive.

00:30:40.966 --> 00:30:44.526 A:middle
And so on iOS 9, we are
bringing proactivity throughout

00:30:44.526 --> 00:30:45.086 A:middle
the system.

00:30:46.086 --> 00:30:48.986 A:middle
So say you like to run in
the morning, and when you do,

00:30:48.986 --> 00:30:50.836 A:middle
you like to listen to music.

00:30:50.836 --> 00:30:53.166 A:middle
Well, now your phone can
learn that about you,

00:30:53.166 --> 00:30:54.526 A:middle
and when you plug
in your headphones,

00:30:55.116 --> 00:30:57.756 A:middle
can offer up Now Playing
automatically right

00:30:57.756 --> 00:30:58.556 A:middle
on the Lock screen.

00:30:59.516 --> 00:31:03.936 A:middle
[Applause]

