Next, let's turn to Maps.

00:48:07.146 --> 00:48:10.116 A:middle
We've continued to
invest heavily in Maps,

00:48:10.176 --> 00:48:12.036 A:middle
and the improvements
are really awesome.

00:48:12.366 --> 00:48:16.186 A:middle
We are seeing five billion
user requests per week.

00:48:17.046 --> 00:48:20.326 A:middle
Usage on iOS is 3.5 times higher

00:48:20.536 --> 00:48:23.726 A:middle
than for the next
leading mapping app.

00:48:23.726 --> 00:48:24.986 A:middle
Now, Maps, of course,

00:48:25.386 --> 00:48:28.786 A:middle
historically have been
focused on drivers.

00:48:29.116 --> 00:48:31.816 A:middle
They emphasize things
like freeways and roads.

00:48:32.466 --> 00:48:37.106 A:middle
But we know for a lot of our iOS
users, they are mostly focused

00:48:37.106 --> 00:48:41.416 A:middle
on public transit, and so now
we've created a great map just

00:48:41.416 --> 00:48:43.526 A:middle
for them.

00:48:43.856 --> 00:48:45.206 A:middle
[Applause] Yes, it's Transit.

00:48:46.516 --> 00:48:49.356 A:middle
[Applause]

00:48:49.856 --> 00:48:52.286 A:middle
With Transit, we provide
a map that emphasizes all

00:48:52.286 --> 00:48:55.576 A:middle
of the different transit
lines, buses, and trains,

00:48:55.576 --> 00:48:58.586 A:middle
subway stations and so forth,
and when you tap on a station,

00:48:59.026 --> 00:49:01.046 A:middle
you can see all the
lines that run through it

WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:181083,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

00:48:59.026 --> 00:49:01.046 A:middle
you can see all the
lines that run through it

00:49:01.266 --> 00:49:02.396 A:middle
with their departure times.

00:49:02.816 --> 00:49:07.376 A:middle
And we do multimodal routing,
whether you are taking a train,

00:49:07.726 --> 00:49:10.056 A:middle
a subway, a bus, or a ferry.

00:49:10.596 --> 00:49:14.066 A:middle
And we provide step-by-step
directions, including time

00:49:14.276 --> 00:49:15.386 A:middle
for walking directions.

00:49:15.386 --> 00:49:19.686 A:middle
But we've taken special care
to get the details right,

00:49:19.826 --> 00:49:21.686 A:middle
the ones that matter,
with Transit.

00:49:22.446 --> 00:49:25.916 A:middle
For instance, if you take a
subway station like this one

00:49:25.916 --> 00:49:30.036 A:middle
in Columbus Circle in New York,
it's not just a point on a map.

00:49:31.016 --> 00:49:32.016 A:middle
If you look closer,

00:49:32.296 --> 00:49:35.536 A:middle
it's actually an enormous
underground structure spanning

00:49:35.536 --> 00:49:40.736 A:middle
many city blocks, and so
we carefully surveyed all

00:49:40.736 --> 00:49:42.606 A:middle
of the entrances and exits

00:49:43.266 --> 00:49:46.166 A:middle
so that we could give you
walking directions based

00:49:46.166 --> 00:49:48.896 A:middle
on the time to travel from
where you actually are.

00:49:49.276 --> 00:49:51.456 A:middle
Now, this not only saves
you a ton of walking,

00:49:51.696 --> 00:49:53.276 A:middle
but it also probably
is the difference

00:49:53.326 --> 00:49:56.096 A:middle
between catching your train
on time and being stuck.

00:49:56.416 --> 00:49:57.836 A:middle
[Applause] It's really great.

00:49:58.516 --> 00:50:04.306 A:middle
[Applause]

