01:05:55.516 --> 01:06:00.856 A:middle
[Applause]

WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:181083,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

01:05:55.516 --> 01:06:00.856 A:middle
[Applause]

01:06:01.356 --> 01:06:04.366 A:middle
So iOS 9 delivers this great
app switcher, and of course,

01:06:04.586 --> 01:06:06.966 A:middle
that's available
on iPhone as well.

01:06:08.036 --> 01:06:11.136 A:middle
On iPad, we have Slide
Over so you can bring apps

01:06:11.136 --> 01:06:11.936 A:middle
in from the side.

01:06:12.596 --> 01:06:14.826 A:middle
You can tap and enter split view

01:06:14.826 --> 01:06:18.336 A:middle
for simultaneous
live two apps up.

01:06:18.796 --> 01:06:20.846 A:middle
And of course, Picture
in Picture.

01:06:21.446 --> 01:06:24.906 A:middle
Now, we provide developer APIs
to let your apps work this way,

01:06:24.906 --> 01:06:28.386 A:middle
and the good news is that you've
already done most of that work

01:06:28.846 --> 01:06:31.816 A:middle
because if you've adopted
Auto Layout and size classes

01:06:31.816 --> 01:06:35.766 A:middle
to work great on the iPhone 6
and 6 Plus, well, that carries

01:06:35.766 --> 01:06:39.786 A:middle
over just like this onto iPad.

01:06:40.076 --> 01:06:42.966 A:middle
Twitter came in and was able
to do it just in minutes.

01:06:42.966 --> 01:06:44.036 A:middle
It was really incredible.

01:06:45.556 --> 01:06:50.686 A:middle
Now, Slide Over is available
for the iPad Air, Air 2, mini 2,

01:06:50.686 --> 01:06:52.956 A:middle
and mini 3, as is
Picture in Picture,

01:06:53.466 --> 01:06:56.006 A:middle
and our most powerful
split view is available

01:06:56.006 --> 01:06:58.976 A:middle
on our most powerful
iPad, the iPad Air 2.

01:06:59.946 --> 01:07:00.686 A:middle
That's Multitasking.

WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:181083,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

01:06:59.946 --> 01:07:00.686 A:middle
That's Multitasking.

01:07:01.516 --> 01:07:09.136 A:middle
[Applause]

01:07:09.636 --> 01:07:12.226 A:middle
So we've seen some
great end-user features,

01:07:12.886 --> 01:07:15.906 A:middle
but of course, we've also
focused on the foundations.

01:07:16.716 --> 01:07:21.956 A:middle
In performance, as you saw
earlier in El Capitan with OS X,

01:07:22.666 --> 01:07:25.636 A:middle
we've taken the core frameworks
that we use for drawing

01:07:25.636 --> 01:07:28.146 A:middle
on the system, Core
Animation and Core Graphics,

01:07:28.146 --> 01:07:29.346 A:middle
and we put them on top of Metal.

01:07:29.346 --> 01:07:31.336 A:middle
We are seeing great
acceleration,

01:07:31.336 --> 01:07:35.116 A:middle
1.6 times improvements in
animations and scrolling,

01:07:35.116 --> 01:07:38.056 A:middle
and a 50 percent reduction
in CPU usage for drawing.

01:07:38.056 --> 01:07:39.006 A:middle
It's really great.

01:07:39.826 --> 01:07:41.846 A:middle
With battery life, we focused

01:07:41.846 --> 01:07:45.246 A:middle
on real-world use cases
and optimized them.

01:07:45.576 --> 01:07:49.816 A:middle
And we are seeing an addition
of one hour of typical use

01:07:49.816 --> 01:07:51.196 A:middle
on a full charge on iPhone.

01:07:52.516 --> 01:07:56.416 A:middle
[Applause]

01:07:56.916 --> 01:07:59.186 A:middle
Now, we know that for a lot
of you if you are running low

01:07:59.186 --> 01:08:01.796 A:middle
on power, you start searching
all over for switches

WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:181083,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

01:07:59.186 --> 01:08:01.796 A:middle
on power, you start searching
all over for switches

01:08:01.796 --> 01:08:03.616 A:middle
and turning off features
in the hope

01:08:03.616 --> 01:08:06.166 A:middle
of extending your battery
life a little bit further.

01:08:06.756 --> 01:08:09.716 A:middle
Well, now in iOS 9, we
give you a single switch

01:08:09.716 --> 01:08:12.746 A:middle
to enter what we call Low
Power mode, and it pulls levers

01:08:12.746 --> 01:08:15.286 A:middle
that you didn't even
know existed and is able

01:08:15.286 --> 01:08:19.845 A:middle
to extend battery life for
an additional three hours

01:08:19.845 --> 01:08:22.185 A:middle
of typical use on top
of that additional hour.

01:08:22.336 --> 01:08:22.975 A:middle
It's really great.

01:08:23.515 --> 01:08:28.816 A:middle
[Applause]

01:08:29.316 --> 01:08:32.265 A:middle
Now, with security, we want
to protect our users' data

01:08:32.366 --> 01:08:33.975 A:middle
on device and in the cloud,

01:08:33.975 --> 01:08:36.616 A:middle
and so we are bringing
two-factor authentication

01:08:36.616 --> 01:08:40.906 A:middle
and making it easy for everyone
to protect their data in iCloud.

01:08:41.576 --> 01:08:46.386 A:middle
And with Software Update, we
want everyone to get to iOS 9,

01:08:46.786 --> 01:08:50.895 A:middle
and so we've done major
enhancements to the architecture

01:08:50.895 --> 01:08:53.136 A:middle
for our over-the-air
updates, and we have been able

01:08:53.136 --> 01:08:56.996 A:middle
to reduce the amount of free
space you need to get to iOS 9

01:08:57.486 --> 01:09:01.206 A:middle
from the 4.6 gigs that
it took to get to iOS 8

WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:181083,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

01:08:57.486 --> 01:09:01.206 A:middle
from the 4.6 gigs that
it took to get to iOS 8

01:09:01.475 --> 01:09:04.166 A:middle
down to just 1.3, so we
think everybody is going

01:09:04.166 --> 01:09:04.966 A:middle
to be getting to iOS 9.

01:09:05.515 --> 01:09:11.196 A:middle
[Applause]

01:09:11.696 --> 01:09:14.376 A:middle
So iOS 9, intelligence
throughout the system,

01:09:14.676 --> 01:09:19.026 A:middle
Apple Pay, enhancements to
really popular apps like Notes

01:09:19.456 --> 01:09:24.866 A:middle
and Maps, an all-new News app,
and incredible features now

01:09:24.866 --> 01:09:27.996 A:middle
for iPad with Multitasking
and QuickType, and of course,

01:09:28.265 --> 01:09:30.126 A:middle
enhancements to the foundations.

01:09:30.626 --> 01:09:35.196 A:middle
Now, iOS 9 is a great release
for our users, but once again,

01:09:35.576 --> 01:09:38.946 A:middle
it's a fantastic release
for all of you developers,

01:09:39.826 --> 01:09:41.326 A:middle
bringing a ton of new features.

01:09:41.326 --> 01:09:42.866 A:middle
You saw search extensibility.

01:09:42.866 --> 01:09:45.786 A:middle
We are adding UI
testing to Xcode.

01:09:45.786 --> 01:09:45.876 A:middle
[Cheers and applause] Yes!

01:09:46.246 --> 01:09:50.566 A:middle
We have a new technology
called App Thinning,

01:09:50.975 --> 01:09:54.145 A:middle
which optimizes your
downloads to exactly the subset

01:09:54.145 --> 01:09:57.146 A:middle
of resources needed for that
user's device, so you are able

01:09:57.146 --> 01:09:59.506 A:middle
to get -- take less
space on device.

01:09:59.506 --> 01:10:00.506 A:middle
It's really great.

WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:181083,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

01:09:59.506 --> 01:10:00.506 A:middle
It's really great.

01:10:01.016 --> 01:10:04.156 A:middle
Now, when it comes to gaming,
we've enhanced SpriteKit,

01:10:04.156 --> 01:10:07.556 A:middle
SceneKit, and Metal and
introduced three new frameworks,

01:10:07.806 --> 01:10:10.316 A:middle
GameplayKit to bring
artificial intelligence

01:10:10.316 --> 01:10:14.306 A:middle
with path avoid obstacle
avoidance and path finding;

01:10:14.646 --> 01:10:16.896 A:middle
Model I/O to provide
beautiful lighting

01:10:16.896 --> 01:10:19.446 A:middle
on your 3D models;
and ReplayKit.

01:10:19.806 --> 01:10:21.956 A:middle
It lets you enhance
your applications

01:10:21.956 --> 01:10:26.116 A:middle
to let users record their game
play as video and share it.

01:10:26.446 --> 01:10:27.266 A:middle
It's really great.

01:10:28.516 --> 01:10:34.546 A:middle
[Applause]

01:10:35.046 --> 01:10:38.726 A:middle
Now, HealthKit has been on
fire, so we've continued --

01:10:38.726 --> 01:10:40.666 A:middle
well, we added water,
actually, to HealthKit.

01:10:40.926 --> 01:10:42.656 A:middle
We are not trying
to put out the fire.

01:10:42.656 --> 01:10:46.616 A:middle
We are adding lots of additional
health metrics to be tracked,

01:10:46.616 --> 01:10:49.666 A:middle
for instance, hydration,
UV exposure,

01:10:49.996 --> 01:10:51.046 A:middle
and reproductive health.

01:10:51.716 --> 01:10:55.016 A:middle
Now, HomeKit has been taking off

01:10:55.486 --> 01:10:57.816 A:middle
with manufacturers
introducing HomeKit peripherals

01:10:57.816 --> 01:11:02.446 A:middle
to the market now in areas like
thermometers, locks, and lights.

WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:181083,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

01:10:57.816 --> 01:11:02.446 A:middle
to the market now in areas like
thermometers, locks, and lights.

01:11:02.976 --> 01:11:05.436 A:middle
And now in iOS 9, we
are adding support

01:11:05.436 --> 01:11:08.436 A:middle
for window shades,
sensors of all kinds.

01:11:08.436 --> 01:11:11.936 A:middle
For instance, carbon monoxide
sensors, motion sensors.

01:11:12.216 --> 01:11:15.576 A:middle
And we're adding support for
security systems as well.

01:11:16.096 --> 01:11:18.636 A:middle
Perhaps most importantly,
we are allowing you

01:11:18.636 --> 01:11:23.456 A:middle
to access your home remotely
and securely via iCloud.

01:11:23.456 --> 01:11:26.256 A:middle
So no matter where you
are, you can control all

01:11:26.256 --> 01:11:27.516 A:middle
of your HomeKit devices.

01:11:28.516 --> 01:11:35.246 A:middle
[Applause]

01:11:35.746 --> 01:11:36.866 A:middle
Next, CarPlay.

01:11:37.256 --> 01:11:42.316 A:middle
So CarPlay supports audio
apps and now, in iOS 9,

01:11:42.506 --> 01:11:46.126 A:middle
it also supports apps by the
automaker to control things

01:11:46.126 --> 01:11:49.876 A:middle
in your own car without
leaving the CarPlay experience.

01:11:50.226 --> 01:11:52.676 A:middle
And CarPlay is supporting
more kinds of screens,

01:11:52.726 --> 01:11:55.006 A:middle
wider aspect ratios, high DPI.

01:11:55.006 --> 01:11:58.406 A:middle
But most significantly
with CarPlay,

01:11:59.036 --> 01:12:00.216 A:middle
we are pulling the cord.

WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:181083,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

01:11:59.036 --> 01:12:00.216 A:middle
we are pulling the cord.

01:12:01.416 --> 01:12:04.566 A:middle
In future cars, you will
be able to get in your car

01:12:04.566 --> 01:12:07.786 A:middle
without taking your phone out of
your bag or out of your pocket

01:12:08.306 --> 01:12:11.966 A:middle
and start experiencing
CarPlay effortlessly.

01:12:12.266 --> 01:12:13.206 A:middle
It's going to be really great.

01:12:14.516 --> 01:12:19.016 A:middle
[Applause]

01:12:19.516 --> 01:12:22.436 A:middle
Finally, let's talk about Swift.

01:12:23.516 --> 01:12:27.996 A:middle
[Cheers and applause]

01:12:28.496 --> 01:12:29.936 A:middle
You all know that the growth

01:12:29.936 --> 01:12:33.546 A:middle
that Swift has been experiencing
is just unprecedented,

01:12:33.546 --> 01:12:35.436 A:middle
and we've all seen
it with the flood

01:12:35.636 --> 01:12:37.986 A:middle
of applications coming
in to the App Store.

01:12:38.906 --> 01:12:43.516 A:middle
Well, now we are stepping on
the gas this year with Swift 2.

01:12:44.206 --> 01:12:47.006 A:middle
Now, Swift was designed from
the beginning to be fast,

01:12:47.536 --> 01:12:48.756 A:middle
and we've continued to roll

01:12:48.756 --> 01:12:52.876 A:middle
out targeted optimizations all
year long, and now with Swift 2,

01:12:52.876 --> 01:12:56.036 A:middle
we have an all-new optimization
technology that's especially

01:12:56.036 --> 01:12:59.266 A:middle
great for complex applications
and object-oriented programming

01:12:59.506 --> 01:13:02.166 A:middle
that we call Whole
Module Optimization,

WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:181083,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

01:12:59.506 --> 01:13:02.166 A:middle
that we call Whole
Module Optimization,

01:13:02.516 --> 01:13:04.736 A:middle
and the results are
really fantastic.

01:13:05.926 --> 01:13:08.556 A:middle
In addition, we are bringing
the language features

01:13:08.556 --> 01:13:10.196 A:middle
that you've asked for most,

01:13:10.456 --> 01:13:12.236 A:middle
an elegant new error
handling model,

01:13:12.616 --> 01:13:14.416 A:middle
the ability to see
your interfaces

01:13:14.416 --> 01:13:17.996 A:middle
as synthesized headers
in Xcode, and the feature

01:13:17.996 --> 01:13:22.346 A:middle
that Tim has been begging for
all year, protocol extensions.

01:13:22.486 --> 01:13:23.506 A:middle
You are all going to love it.

01:13:25.176 --> 01:13:30.646 A:middle
Now, we think Swift is the
next big programming language,

01:13:30.676 --> 01:13:32.846 A:middle
the one that we will
all be doing application

01:13:33.146 --> 01:13:37.026 A:middle
and systems programming
on for 20 years to come.

01:13:37.986 --> 01:13:42.916 A:middle
And we think Swift should be
everywhere and used by everyone,

01:13:43.576 --> 01:13:45.876 A:middle
and so we're going to be
doing something really big.

01:13:46.606 --> 01:13:50.666 A:middle
Today we are announcing that
Swift will be open source.

01:13:51.516 --> 01:14:14.406 A:middle
[Cheers and applause]

WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:181083,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

01:13:51.516 --> 01:14:14.406 A:middle
[Cheers and applause]

01:14:14.906 --> 01:14:16.646 A:middle
We will be rolling
out the compiler

01:14:17.876 --> 01:14:21.836 A:middle
and the standard libraries
for iOS, OS X, and Linux.

01:14:22.986 --> 01:14:27.766 A:middle
And it will all be out there
by the end of the year.

01:14:28.606 --> 01:14:30.566 A:middle
So that's Swift,
and that is iOS 9.

01:14:30.566 --> 01:14:33.776 A:middle
We are doing a developer
beta -- you guessed it --

01:14:33.776 --> 01:14:36.916 A:middle
today, and for the first
time for a major iOS release,

01:14:36.956 --> 01:14:40.676 A:middle
a public beta, so sign
up now at beta.apple.com,

01:14:40.806 --> 01:14:43.056 A:middle
and you can get the beta
when it comes out in July.

01:14:43.136 --> 01:14:45.096 A:middle
And of course, we
will be rolling it

01:14:45.096 --> 01:14:46.776 A:middle
out as a free upgrade
in the fall.

01:14:47.176 --> 01:14:51.976 A:middle
And iOS 9 will support
all of the devices

01:14:51.976 --> 01:14:53.686 A:middle
that were supported by iOS 8.

01:14:53.686 --> 01:14:55.086 A:middle
We are not dropping
any this year

01:14:55.086 --> 01:14:57.676 A:middle
because we want everyone
to get iOS 9.

01:14:58.016 --> 01:14:59.916 A:middle
[Applause]

01:14:59.916 --> 01:15:00.506 A:middle
That's iOS 9.

WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:181083,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

01:14:59.916 --> 01:15:00.506 A:middle
That's iOS 9.

