01:24:54.086 --> 01:24:58.396 A:middle
Now, we want to talk about
now the next opportunity

01:24:58.396 --> 01:24:59.596 A:middle
to transform the world.

01:24:59.596 --> 01:25:06.016 A:middle
And that's the opportunity to
bring native apps to the Watch

WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:181083,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

01:24:59.596 --> 01:25:06.016 A:middle
And that's the opportunity to
bring native apps to the Watch

01:25:06.336 --> 01:25:08.816 A:middle
with a new version of watchOS.

01:25:09.516 --> 01:25:14.566 A:middle
[Applause]

01:25:15.066 --> 01:25:18.886 A:middle
For us, this is a giant moment.

01:25:20.306 --> 01:25:24.056 A:middle
This is how we felt when
we launched the App Store.

01:25:24.916 --> 01:25:27.306 A:middle
Opening a new platform
to developers

01:25:28.016 --> 01:25:31.916 A:middle
to create new applications

01:25:32.786 --> 01:25:34.826 A:middle
that can really change
people's lives.

01:25:36.346 --> 01:25:38.396 A:middle
We really believe
deeply in this space.

01:25:38.456 --> 01:25:41.486 A:middle
We believe in technology
designed for the wrist.

01:25:42.876 --> 01:25:45.156 A:middle
And we believe by
opening up the platform

01:25:45.156 --> 01:25:49.756 A:middle
that you will create
new and powerful uses

01:25:50.436 --> 01:25:52.956 A:middle
that today we can
only begin to imagine.

01:25:53.696 --> 01:25:59.266 A:middle
We began making the Apple Watch
available just six weeks ago,

01:25:59.266 --> 01:26:04.186 A:middle
and it's pretty amazing that
today we're already talking

WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:181083,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

01:25:59.266 --> 01:26:04.186 A:middle
and it's pretty amazing that
today we're already talking

01:26:04.186 --> 01:26:07.386 A:middle
about the next version
of the watchOS.

01:26:08.366 --> 01:26:12.536 A:middle
This new version will have
great new capabilities,

01:26:13.326 --> 01:26:16.556 A:middle
and it will bring native
apps right to your wrist.

01:26:17.706 --> 01:26:22.326 A:middle
To tell you all about it, I'd
like to invite up my friend

01:26:22.326 --> 01:26:24.576 A:middle
and colleague Kevin Lynch.

01:26:24.766 --> 01:26:24.976 A:middle
Kevin.

01:26:25.516 --> 01:26:29.856 A:middle
[Cheers and applause]

01:26:30.356 --> 01:26:30.786 A:middle
&gt;&gt; KEVIN LYNCH: Hi.

01:26:33.496 --> 01:26:37.066 A:middle
So we're moving really fast on
watchOS, and I am super excited

01:26:37.066 --> 01:26:39.076 A:middle
to talk with you about the
enhancements that are coming

01:26:39.076 --> 01:26:40.606 A:middle
in watchOS, as well

01:26:40.606 --> 01:26:43.006 A:middle
as the powerful new
abilities for app development.

01:26:43.406 --> 01:26:44.836 A:middle
Let's start with
the enhancements.

01:26:45.836 --> 01:26:49.146 A:middle
The enhancements include
great new Timepiece functions,

01:26:49.526 --> 01:26:52.346 A:middle
improvements in communication
as well as in Health &amp; Fitness,

01:26:52.446 --> 01:26:54.226 A:middle
and support for the
new capabilities

01:26:54.226 --> 01:26:56.386 A:middle
in Apple Pay, Maps, and Siri.

01:26:56.886 --> 01:26:58.256 A:middle
Let's start with Timepiece.

01:26:59.076 --> 01:27:02.096 A:middle
Now, already, Apple Watch
is a really great timepiece,

WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:181083,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

01:26:59.076 --> 01:27:02.096 A:middle
Now, already, Apple Watch
is a really great timepiece,

01:27:02.096 --> 01:27:04.776 A:middle
the most customizable one in the
world, and a lot of that is due

01:27:04.776 --> 01:27:06.776 A:middle
to the Watch faces and
how you can change them.

01:27:07.026 --> 01:27:09.436 A:middle
We are adding some new
Watch faces in watchOS 2.

01:27:10.196 --> 01:27:12.896 A:middle
That includes a beautiful
new Photos face to be able

01:27:12.896 --> 01:27:15.576 A:middle
to select any photo you have and
create a Watch face out of it.

01:27:15.576 --> 01:27:18.506 A:middle
You can create more than one and
switch between them as you like.

01:27:19.136 --> 01:27:20.616 A:middle
Or you can select a photo album,

01:27:20.896 --> 01:27:22.216 A:middle
and every time you
raise your wrist,

01:27:22.216 --> 01:27:24.506 A:middle
you will see a different
photo from your album show up.

01:27:24.506 --> 01:27:27.136 A:middle
It's a great way of seeing
your photos throughout the day.

01:27:27.696 --> 01:27:30.126 A:middle
We went a little
further with this,

01:27:30.126 --> 01:27:31.566 A:middle
and we shot some
photos ourselves.

01:27:31.566 --> 01:27:33.096 A:middle
We did some time-lapse
photography

01:27:33.096 --> 01:27:34.866 A:middle
in some beautiful
locations around the world.

01:27:35.656 --> 01:27:37.286 A:middle
The way this works is
when you raise your wrist,

01:27:37.566 --> 01:27:39.826 A:middle
you will see this
24-hour shoot we have done

01:27:39.826 --> 01:27:42.646 A:middle
in different locations, and it
will be the current time there.

01:27:42.646 --> 01:27:44.306 A:middle
If it's in noon, you
will see noon in London.

01:27:44.566 --> 01:27:46.596 A:middle
If it's night, you'll
see Big Ben all lit up.

01:27:46.916 --> 01:27:48.286 A:middle
We've done this not
only for London,

01:27:48.286 --> 01:27:49.596 A:middle
but some other locations too.

01:27:49.916 --> 01:27:52.116 A:middle
You can choose from
Hong Kong, Mack Lake --

01:27:52.116 --> 01:27:53.786 A:middle
which a beautiful
place in the Sierras --

01:27:53.786 --> 01:27:56.586 A:middle
as well as New York,
Shanghai, and London.

01:27:57.306 --> 01:28:00.146 A:middle
It's a great way to see really
beautiful imagery, both your own

WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:181083,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

01:27:57.306 --> 01:28:00.146 A:middle
It's a great way to see really
beautiful imagery, both your own

01:28:00.146 --> 01:28:01.886 A:middle
and these time-lapse
images, on your wrist.

01:28:01.886 --> 01:28:05.166 A:middle
You can customize your
Watch with these images

01:28:05.416 --> 01:28:07.516 A:middle
but you can also choose to
show the information that you

01:28:07.516 --> 01:28:10.056 A:middle
like on your Watch
face with something

01:28:10.056 --> 01:28:12.656 A:middle
in traditional Watch terms
that's called Complications.

01:28:13.396 --> 01:28:17.116 A:middle
With watchOS 2, we are really
excited to enable app developers

01:28:17.276 --> 01:28:18.866 A:middle
to make your own Complications.

01:28:19.516 --> 01:28:25.936 A:middle
[Applause]

01:28:26.436 --> 01:28:29.086 A:middle
So be able to do things
like show your flight time

01:28:29.086 --> 01:28:32.036 A:middle
from United, see the state
of your home control system,

01:28:32.316 --> 01:28:34.396 A:middle
look at the charge level
of your electric car,

01:28:34.596 --> 01:28:37.066 A:middle
or see sports scores, for
example, from the MLB app.

01:28:37.326 --> 01:28:38.896 A:middle
You can choose the
information that you most

01:28:38.896 --> 01:28:40.716 A:middle
like to see right
on your Watch face.

01:28:40.806 --> 01:28:42.246 A:middle
It's going to be
really, really cool.

01:28:42.596 --> 01:28:44.396 A:middle
And this will work not
only on the modular face

01:28:44.756 --> 01:28:47.136 A:middle
but across the others that
support Complications as well.

01:28:47.136 --> 01:28:49.546 A:middle
You will be able to choose
from a variety of templates,

01:28:49.546 --> 01:28:51.316 A:middle
and we'll make those
look beautiful in each

01:28:51.316 --> 01:28:52.456 A:middle
of the different Watch faces.

01:28:53.226 --> 01:28:54.616 A:middle
So it's going to be
a really fast way

01:28:54.616 --> 01:28:55.726 A:middle
to look at this information.

01:28:56.496 --> 01:28:57.596 A:middle
Now, we went further than this.

01:28:57.596 --> 01:28:59.256 A:middle
We thought it's really
great to be able

01:28:59.256 --> 01:29:00.486 A:middle
to see the current information,

WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:181083,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

01:28:59.256 --> 01:29:00.486 A:middle
to see the current information,

01:29:00.936 --> 01:29:02.386 A:middle
but what about future
information,

01:29:02.386 --> 01:29:05.096 A:middle
like the weather later
today or your meeting

01:29:05.096 --> 01:29:06.566 A:middle
after the current one?

01:29:07.036 --> 01:29:09.226 A:middle
And what if you could go
forward in time and actually see

01:29:09.226 --> 01:29:11.076 A:middle
that information update
on your Watch face?

01:29:11.986 --> 01:29:13.756 A:middle
Well, we are supporting
that in watchOS 2

01:29:13.756 --> 01:29:15.806 A:middle
with something we
call Time Travel.

01:29:16.556 --> 01:29:18.866 A:middle
And you will be able to
rotate your Digital Crown,

01:29:18.866 --> 01:29:21.426 A:middle
and you can go both forward
and backward through time,

01:29:21.426 --> 01:29:23.886 A:middle
and the information will
update right on your screen.

01:29:24.546 --> 01:29:25.356 A:middle
Let's take a look here.

01:29:25.976 --> 01:29:28.536 A:middle
So I've got my meeting in
the middle there and weather

01:29:28.536 --> 01:29:30.656 A:middle
and the charge level of
the car and time in London.

01:29:31.006 --> 01:29:33.776 A:middle
When I rotate the Crown, you
can see it's changing the time

01:29:33.776 --> 01:29:35.276 A:middle
and showing me things
that are coming up.

01:29:36.006 --> 01:29:38.196 A:middle
Now, we know a really popular
one here might be the stocks

01:29:38.196 --> 01:29:40.046 A:middle
Complication, but we
haven't cracked that one yet.

01:29:40.366 --> 01:29:43.596 A:middle
We are working on it.

01:29:44.256 --> 01:29:46.206 A:middle
You can keep rotating,
keep going forward,

01:29:46.206 --> 01:29:47.186 A:middle
get all the way to tonight.

01:29:47.186 --> 01:29:49.436 A:middle
You can see I have a date
night tonight, weather is going

01:29:49.436 --> 01:29:52.116 A:middle
to be good, time in London will
be 2:00 a.m. You can see all the

01:29:52.116 --> 01:29:55.286 A:middle
information you like to see in
the time you want to look at it.

01:29:55.286 --> 01:29:57.416 A:middle
Really, really fun
way to interact

01:29:57.786 --> 01:29:59.186 A:middle
with time on your Watch.

WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:181083,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

01:30:00.136 --> 01:30:01.976 A:middle
That's Time Travel.

01:30:02.516 --> 01:30:07.446 A:middle
[Applause]

01:30:07.946 --> 01:30:10.616 A:middle
Now, we also thought, What
would be a great experience

01:30:10.616 --> 01:30:12.676 A:middle
for the Watch when it's on
your nightstand and charging?

01:30:13.306 --> 01:30:15.406 A:middle
Well, we've come up with a
new user interface for this

01:30:15.406 --> 01:30:17.556 A:middle
in watchOS 2 called
Nightstand Mode.

01:30:18.036 --> 01:30:20.046 A:middle
When you put your Watch on
its side and it's charging,

01:30:20.246 --> 01:30:22.226 A:middle
you will get this beautiful
display now of the time,

01:30:22.706 --> 01:30:24.736 A:middle
and of course, you can set
an alarm that will wake you

01:30:24.736 --> 01:30:27.196 A:middle
up in the morning, and it
will go something like this.

01:30:28.241 --> 01:30:30.241 A:middle
[Alarm tone]

01:30:30.466 --> 01:30:32.536 A:middle
So a beautiful little
bedside alarm clock now

01:30:32.536 --> 01:30:35.116 A:middle
with Apple Watch, and
the buttons on the side

01:30:35.116 --> 01:30:38.666 A:middle
and the Crown act as your
Snooze and your Off button.

01:30:38.666 --> 01:30:41.776 A:middle
A really fun way to have a
Nightstand view on your Watch.

01:30:42.156 --> 01:30:44.866 A:middle
Those are some of the great
new Timepiece functions

01:30:44.866 --> 01:30:46.256 A:middle
that are coming in watchOS 2.

01:30:47.406 --> 01:30:48.526 A:middle
Let's look at communication.

01:30:49.016 --> 01:30:50.396 A:middle
Now, already Apple
Watch is great

01:30:50.396 --> 01:30:51.676 A:middle
at communicating
with your friends.

01:30:52.046 --> 01:30:55.076 A:middle
You can just press the side
button and see your 12 friends

01:30:55.076 --> 01:30:55.766 A:middle
that you have selected.

01:30:56.296 --> 01:30:58.236 A:middle
Now, we realize that some of
you have more than 12 friends,

01:30:58.586 --> 01:31:01.576 A:middle
so now in watchOS 2, you
can have different sets

WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:181083,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

01:30:58.586 --> 01:31:01.576 A:middle
so now in watchOS 2, you
can have different sets

01:31:01.576 --> 01:31:04.246 A:middle
of friends you can select,
and you can add a friend right

01:31:04.246 --> 01:31:05.906 A:middle
from your Watch by
pressing the plus sign

01:31:06.136 --> 01:31:07.606 A:middle
and add a friend right there.

01:31:08.766 --> 01:31:09.566 A:middle
Isn't that cool?

01:31:10.516 --> 01:31:13.086 A:middle
[Applause]

01:31:13.586 --> 01:31:14.746 A:middle
Now, when you are
communicating with someone,

