the mass transit capabilities
in Maps now, so you will be able

01:33:22.486 --> 01:33:23.976 A:middle
to see the transit
lines on your wrist.

01:33:24.366 --> 01:33:25.986 A:middle
You can actually see
the departure times

01:33:25.986 --> 01:33:27.186 A:middle
for different stations
you are near.

01:33:27.596 --> 01:33:30.016 A:middle
When you are navigating, you
will get step-by-step directions

01:33:30.296 --> 01:33:32.326 A:middle
about getting through the
different mass transit you use.

01:33:33.296 --> 01:33:36.156 A:middle
With Siri, we are continuing
to add new domains for Siri.

01:33:36.466 --> 01:33:38.646 A:middle
In watchOS 2, we
are enabling Siri

01:33:38.646 --> 01:33:41.046 A:middle
to get you mass transit
directions, like bus directions

01:33:41.046 --> 01:33:42.806 A:middle
to the Ferry Building,
which will look like this

01:33:42.806 --> 01:33:44.076 A:middle
and you can just
start navigating.

01:33:44.506 --> 01:33:46.866 A:middle
Or you can control things
in your home with Siri,

01:33:47.266 --> 01:33:49.946 A:middle
you can say things like "hey
Siri set the dinner scene,"

01:33:49.946 --> 01:33:52.406 A:middle
and it will talk to any
HomeKit-enabled devices

01:33:52.406 --> 01:33:54.906 A:middle
in your house and set the
lights just how you want them.

01:33:55.386 --> 01:33:57.136 A:middle
Isn't that cool?

01:33:57.686 --> 01:33:58.926 A:middle
It's going to be great.

01:33:59.516 --> 01:34:02.546 A:middle
[Applause]

WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:181083,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

01:33:59.516 --> 01:34:02.546 A:middle
[Applause]

