Another great thing is you
can actually ask for any

01:34:05.216 --> 01:34:07.846 A:middle
of the Glances you have,
so you can say "hey, Siri,

01:34:07.846 --> 01:34:10.026 A:middle
show me the Instagram
Glance," and it will show

01:34:10.026 --> 01:34:11.036 A:middle
up right on your Watch face.

01:34:11.346 --> 01:34:13.586 A:middle
This could be a glance you
don't have currently selected.

01:34:13.866 --> 01:34:15.716 A:middle
It's a great way
to show information

01:34:15.716 --> 01:34:17.876 A:middle
from third-party apps
right there in Siri.

01:34:19.296 --> 01:34:20.716 A:middle
So those are just
some of the highlights

01:34:20.716 --> 01:34:22.146 A:middle
of what's coming in watchOS 2.

01:34:22.146 --> 01:34:23.146 A:middle
We think it's going
to be a really,

01:34:23.146 --> 01:34:24.686 A:middle
really great update
to the Watch.

01:34:26.266 --> 01:34:26.936 A:middle
Now, that's not all.

01:34:27.516 --> 01:34:30.956 A:middle
[Applause]

01:34:31.456 --> 01:34:34.356 A:middle
We also, of course, focused on
what we can do for developers,

01:34:34.736 --> 01:34:37.686 A:middle
and already, out of the gate
on day one, you can build apps

01:34:37.716 --> 01:34:40.026 A:middle
for Apple Watch using
something called WatchKit,

01:34:40.026 --> 01:34:43.826 A:middle
and that has enabled many
thousands of apps now

01:34:43.946 --> 01:34:47.036 A:middle
to be created for Apple Watch,
and these apps today function

01:34:47.196 --> 01:34:48.336 A:middle
by relying on your phone.

01:34:48.816 --> 01:34:50.786 A:middle
So you might have, for
example, an app on your Watch

01:34:50.966 --> 01:34:52.696 A:middle
and the user interface
runs on your phone

01:34:53.036 --> 01:34:55.676 A:middle
and the user interface is on
your Watch, but all the logic

01:34:55.676 --> 01:34:57.826 A:middle
for your app today
runs on your phone.

01:34:58.126 --> 01:35:00.676 A:middle
With native apps, you will
be able to move that logic

WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:181083,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

01:34:58.126 --> 01:35:00.676 A:middle
With native apps, you will
be able to move that logic

01:35:00.746 --> 01:35:03.456 A:middle
to the watch so both the
UI and the logic are there,

01:35:03.456 --> 01:35:06.006 A:middle
it will all run locally,
performance will be great,

01:35:06.096 --> 01:35:07.266 A:middle
responsiveness will be great,

01:35:07.266 --> 01:35:09.776 A:middle
it's going to be a great new
frontier for apps on Apple Watch

01:35:09.816 --> 01:35:10.926 A:middle
with native app support.

01:35:11.516 --> 01:35:17.476 A:middle
[Applause]

01:35:17.976 --> 01:35:20.486 A:middle
When you are actually wandering
away from your phone sometimes,

01:35:20.876 --> 01:35:22.436 A:middle
your apps will be able
to communicate directly

01:35:22.436 --> 01:35:24.276 A:middle
with the network with
known Wi-Fi networks,

01:35:24.476 --> 01:35:26.466 A:middle
so you can get the information
you want wherever you are

01:35:26.466 --> 01:35:27.186 A:middle
with your Watch.

01:35:28.516 --> 01:35:32.196 A:middle
[Applause]

