We also heard you want to
play audio out of the speaker.

01:36:02.976 --> 01:36:03.646 A:middle
You can do that.

01:36:03.646 --> 01:36:05.636 A:middle
WatchOS 2 with native
apps, you can play back

01:36:05.636 --> 01:36:07.996 A:middle
through the Watch speaker
or you can play audio

01:36:08.226 --> 01:36:10.286 A:middle
to a Bluetooth headset
or speaker connected,

01:36:10.286 --> 01:36:12.136 A:middle
both short-form and
long-form audio.

01:36:12.666 --> 01:36:14.406 A:middle
Video. We know you
wanted to play video.

01:36:14.406 --> 01:36:16.816 A:middle
You can play back short-form
video right on the Watch face.

01:36:16.816 --> 01:36:18.756 A:middle
It looks beautiful
on the Watch display.

01:36:19.866 --> 01:36:20.966 A:middle
Access to HealthKit.

01:36:21.456 --> 01:36:22.436 A:middle
We definitely heard that.

01:36:22.756 --> 01:36:25.156 A:middle
You now will have access,
native HealthKit on the watch,

01:36:25.496 --> 01:36:28.186 A:middle
including streaming heart rate
data, so if you are doing,

01:36:28.186 --> 01:36:29.996 A:middle
for example, a bike
ride with Strava,

01:36:29.996 --> 01:36:32.306 A:middle
you can see what heart rate zone
you are in while you are biking.

01:36:33.516 --> 01:36:38.396 A:middle
[Applause]

